text:
@TriggeredInsaan Let A= x+i(y)
B=p+i(q)
C=m+i(n) and D= a+i(b)
Given A+B=C, so 
(x+p)^2 +(y+q)^2 = m^2 +n^2.
Given B+C=D, so
(p+m)^2 +(q+n)^2= a^2+b^2.
since m=x+p and n= y+q, 
(x+2p)^2 +(y+2q)^2 = a^2+b^2
Therefore,
 |D|^2 = |(x+2p)+i(y+2q)|^2
 =|[x+i(y)]+ 2[p+i(q)]|^2 
D=A+2B, A+C=A+A+B=D
